layout.p:
Columns: 1 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 16 26;
                                                  written lines: 15 25; Uniform layout.Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.Initial words written in larger characters.Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.Numerous marginal notes and additions in different handwritings.Watermark on folio [405 recto] of a monogram VCF. Instead of catchwords, the end and the beginning of the quires are numbered with Hebrew characters included into decorated panels starting with alef (numerical value 1) on folios 15v-16r.Folio 7 is bound upside down.Numerous words and passages have been crossed out by a censor (e.g., folios 17r, 38r, 42v, 49v, 57r, 61r, 70r, 86r, 107v, 147r, 173r, 174v, 215r, 263r, 377v, 397r; entire poems, e.g., folios 58v-59v, 291v, 382v-383v).
